\title{potytools: Analysis Tools for Potyvirus Genomics and Short Linear Motifs}
\description{
Functions for potyvirus genomic analysis: GenBank parsing, codon-usage
bias, host classification, motif-flank extraction and concatenation, and
phylogenetic utilities.

Provides functions for potyvirus genomic analysis, including GenBank file parsing (no external dependencies), codon usage bias calculation (RSCU, ENC, CAI, GC content), host classification for monocot/dicot-infecting isolates, motif-flanking region extraction and concatenation for short-linear-motif analysis, and phylogenetic utilities. Designed for reproducible analysis of Potyviridae diversity, DNAzyme-like motif conservation, and horizontal gene transfer detection.
}
